            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Lucius Herennius Certus lived for 13 years. Farewell!</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#AA">
                <p>The gens Herennia is extremely well attested in the republican period, in both literary and numismatic sources, see Bivona (1994) for references. A Herennia Polla also belongs to Thermae Himeraeae, see <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000182">ISic000182</ref>, and for elsewhere in Sicily, <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000496">ISic000496</ref> and <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000561">ISic000561</ref>, all of which are imperial in date.</p>
            </div>
